\tab Nomad centers around the idea of limited resources.  The player will travel from map to map, trying to scrounge up enough resources to survive, and make it to the next system.  The player will acquire resources by pillaging dead plants, stealing them from other factions, or salvaging them from abandoned ships.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\nowidctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af9\afs24\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200{\cf1\kerning1\langfe2052\dbch\af9\afs24\alang1081\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3
\tab The player will command a small fleet of ships, with a normal fleet being between five to ten ships.  The player will have limited control over each ships equipment, allowing the player to balance between fire power, armor, and speed.  Certain ships will be equipped with RU refineries to allow for field production of certain resources.  All other resources will be produced at the foundry.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\nowidctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af9\afs24\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa200{\cf1\kerning1\langfe2052\dbch\af9\afs24\alang1081\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3
